# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>
#
# Types:
#   feat:     A new feature
#   fix:      A bug fix
#   docs:     Documentation only changes
#   style:    Changes that do not affect the meaning of the code
#   refactor: A code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf:     A performance improvement
#   test:     Adding missing tests or correcting existing tests
#   build:    Changes that affect the build system or external dependencies
#   ci:       Changes to CI configuration files and scripts
#   chore:    Other changes that don't modify src or test files
#   revert:   Reverts a previous commit
#
# Scope (optional):
#   api, rss, database, config, docker, ci, docs, tests, deployment
#
# Subject:
#   - Use imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#   - Don't capitalize first letter
#   - No period (.) at the end
#   - Maximum 50 characters
#
# Body (optional):
#   - Explain what and why vs. how
#   - Wrap at 72 characters
#   - Can use multiple paragraphs
#
# Footer (optional):
#   - Reference issues: Closes #123, Fixes #456
#   - BREAKING CHANGE: describe breaking changes
#
# Examples:
#   feat(rss): add RSS feed item limit configuration
#   fix(api): resolve database connection leak on shutdown
#   docs: update deployment guide for Windows Server
#   test(rss): add validation tests for RSS 2.0 compliance
#   perf(database): optimize article query with indexing
#   build(docker): reduce image size with multi-stage build
#   ci: add pre-commit hooks for code quality checks
#
